cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DB 

The paper discusses the development of a technical framework for enhancing scientific retrieval processes, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of co-authorship networks also suggests a potential fit with social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of metadata and OAI-PMH suggests a potential fit with databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE).
